Description: CVE-2026-50264 - dri2: deduplicate attachments to fix OOB heap write
 An out-of-bounds heap write in DRIGetBuffers / DRIGetBuffersWithFormat
 allows a local X11 client that requests multiple DRI2BufferBackLeft
 attachments together with one DRI2BufferFrontLeft to drive the buffers
 array index past its allocation, corrupting the heap. Impact: server
 crash or privilege escalation when the X server runs as root
 (CWE-787, CVSS 7.8). Reported by Peter Hutterer (Red Hat).
 .
 This backport squashes two upstream commits applied in order:
   * b7aa65cc3bb1 "dri2: Use booleans for (fake) front buffer tracking
     in do_get_buffers" (preparatory refactor: replace int counters with
     Bool flags so duplicate client requests cannot drive the counters
     past zero).
   * 339c27951432 "dri2: Deduplicate attachments in do_get_buffer"
     (primary fix: reject attachments > DRI2BufferHiz, deduplicate via a
     bit-set, and cap the buffers allocation at DRI2BufferHiz + 1 so the
     loop index can never exceed the allocated size).
Origin: upstream, https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/xorg/xserver/-/commit/b7aa65cc3bb11b792ce2a3f511ba9b863acb11c8
Origin: upstream, https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/xorg/xserver/-/commit/339c279514326134b0878fc23ce6e9520440ce7f
