Description: Fix CVE-2026-50261 use-after-free in SyncChangeCounter
 When a trigger fires via SyncAwaitTriggerFired, the subsequent
 FreeResource/FreeAwait call invokes SyncDeleteTriggerFromSyncObject for
 every trigger in the same Await group, which unlinks and frees the
 corresponding trigger list nodes - potentially including the node pnext
 points to. Restart iteration from the list head after a trigger fires,
 since TriggerFired may have mutated the list arbitrarily. Triggers which
 have already fired are removed by FreeAwait, so restarting will not cause
 infinite loops.
 .
 Reported by an anonymous researcher working with Trend Micro's Zero Day
 Initiative (ZDI-CAN-30164).
